From: virtual.c host address space probing fix
Subject: ntdll: Don't probe host address space limit on x86_64

Use the static address_space_limit value on x86_64 instead of dynamically
probing with mmap, which causes ~30+ ENOMEM failures per process probing
into kernel address space. This triggers memory map state corruption that
leads to a NULL-pointer double-fault crash after the anti-cheat breakpoint
in League of Legends.

diff --git a/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c b/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
index 111849d..8666895 100644
--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/virtual.c
@@ -3654,7 +3654,7 @@ void virtual_init(void)
     TRACE( "host page size: %uk\n", (UINT)host_page_size / 1024 );
 #endif
 
-#ifdef _WIN64
+#ifdef __aarch64__
     host_addr_space_limit = get_host_addr_space_limit();
     TRACE( "host addr space limit: %p\n", host_addr_space_limit );
 #else
